By way of derogation from Article 2(1), Member States shall from 1 May to 31 August 2004 authorise the trade in products referred to in Article 1 which are obtained in establishments authorised to export to the Community provided that the products:
(a) bear the Community export health mark of the establishments concerned;
(b) are accompanied by a document as set out in the Directives referred to in Article 1 in which the competent authority of the new Member States of origin certifies the following:
